        <div class="num">N°01 — the problem</div>
        <h2>"It's not aging.<br>It's <em>depletion.</em>"</h2>
        <p>We started where every supplement project starts — by looking at what the bestselling products on the shelf actually contained, and asking what people were trying to fix.</p>
        <p>The fix list was the same across thousands of customer interviews: <strong>brain fog at 3pm</strong>, <strong>slower recovery</strong>, <strong>fragmented sleep</strong>, <strong>a dimmer energy baseline.</strong> Most people had been blaming aging. But the symptoms were responding to mineral and nootropic replenishment in <em>weeks</em> — not the years aging takes.</p>
        <p>It wasn't aging. It was depletion.</p>
        <blockquote class="pull">Modern life is mineral-depleting at a rate the supplement industry has not caught up to.<span class="by">— Internal IONIQ founding memo, 2024</span></blockquote>
